ll\" and I would probably be less likely to miss the post.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nRelated proposals:\r\n\r\n* [There should be a tag for “shell” ](https://lobste.rs/s/fwjofs/there_should_be_tag_for_shell) (95)\r\n* [Tag Proposal: shell](https://lobste.rs/s/3rpinm/tag_proposal_shell) (42)\r\n\r\nFor the reasons above, I think `cli` is a better tag than `shell`:\r\n\r\n* people who are interested in shells are interested in all the tooling above and below them\r\n* we don't need to nitpick what exactly belongs to a shell or not, and if there is a certain overlap with other tags (like rust), that is perfectly normal\r\n\r\nYES: PowerShell, Oils, tmux, Bubble Tea, Elvish, pgcli, tmux\r\n\r\nNO: Python, Perl, Homebrew, Docker","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/xq3zt9/case_for_cli_tag","submitter_user":"felixyz","user_is_author":true,"tags":["meta"]},{"short_id":"etdcng","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/etdcng","created_at":"2024-03-19T19:09:36.000-05:00","title":"Trailing Dots in Domain Names","url":"http://www.dns-sd.org/trailingdotsindomainnames.html","score":31,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/etdcng/trailing_dots_domain_names","submitter_user":"l0b0","user_is_author":false,"tags":["networking"]}]